        "modelCardInfo": {
          "botName": "Computer Build AI Assistant",
          "description": "This AI tool is here to guide you through choosing parts for a fictional computer build. It asks about things like budget, purpose (gaming, content creation, etc.), and personal preferences, then recommends specific components. Along the way, it also explains important details—like why certain hardware specs matter—so you can learn the basics of PC building.",
          "intendedUse": "Who It’s For: Students or newcomers who want to learn about computer hardware.\n\nWhat It Does: \n* Asks about your needs and preferences. \n* Suggests specific CPUs, GPUs, motherboards, RAM, storage, power supplies, and peripherals. \n* Explains complex hardware terms in a clear, beginner-friendly way.",
          "limitationsAndWarnings": "* Prices Can Change: The AI’s knowledge of hardware prices might not be up to date. Always double-check current pricing.\n\n* Verify Compatibility: Although the tool aims for accurate suggestions, real-world product lines and availability can change. Confirm any recommended parts with a trusted retailer or resource.\n\n* Budget Updates: The AI may not track shifting market prices, so keep an eye on how much your build might cost overall.",
          "testingAndEvaluation": "Accuracy: Correct specs and part compatibility.\n\nClarity: Simple, understandable language for beginners.\n\nRelevance: Does the AI’s suggestion match your specific needs?",
